I closed one of the biggest remaining spec gaps on the app side: user input and permission/question resolution now go through the v3 `SyncNode` path instead of silently falling back to the legacy transport.

`[sync.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/sync.ts#L505)` now sends user messages through `[syncNodeStore.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/syncNodeStore.ts#L154)` with v3 message metadata attached. `[ops.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/ops.ts#L354)` now resolves permissions and questions only through `AppSyncStore`/`SyncNode`, including correct `"always"` mapping for session-wide approvals. `[AskUserQuestionView.tsx](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/components/tools/views/AskUserQuestionView.tsx#L238)` now submits structured answers over the v3 channel instead of approving a legacy prompt and sending free-form text, and `[toolPartToToolCall.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/components/parts/toolPartToToolCall.ts#L8)` makes blocked question tools render with the pending interaction metadata the UI needs. I also preserved user-facing `displayText` in `[V3MessageView.tsx](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/components/parts/V3MessageView.tsx#L44)`.

Verified with `yarn workspace happy-app typecheck` and `yarn workspace happy-app vitest run sources/sync/ops.spec.ts sources/components/parts/ToolPartView.test.ts`.

The full monorepo refactor plan is still larger than this change set; the main remaining work is the older CLI/app legacy transport cleanup outside this app-side message/permission/question flow.
